            <title>[LUCENE-385] [PATCH] don&apos;t delete all files in index directory on index creation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-385</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Many people use Lucene to index a part of their file system. The chance that  &lt;br/&gt;
you some day mix up index directory and document directory isn&apos;t that bad.  &lt;br/&gt;
Currently Lucene will delete &lt;b&gt;all&lt;/b&gt; files in the index directory when the  &lt;br/&gt;
create paramater passed to IndexWriter is true, thus deleting your documents &lt;br/&gt;
if you mixed up the parameters. I&apos;ll attach a patch that fixes  &lt;br/&gt;
this. Any objections?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
